[Gaon Chart]]|language=Korean |accessdate=3 December 2010}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" | [[Korea K-Pop Hot 100|Billboard<br>K-Pop<br>Hot 100]]<ref name=\"Hot100Kpop\">{{cite web |title=Korea K-Pop Hot 100 |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/k-pop-hot-100 |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |accessdate=13 March 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" |2011\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Dream High (\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud558\uc774)\"\n<small>(with [[JOO (singer)|JOO]], [[Taecyeon]], [[Bae Suzy|Suzy]],   Wooyoung, IU)</small>\n| 23 || \u2014 \n|rowspan=\"2\" |''[[Dream High#Soundtrack|Dream High: Original Sound Track]]''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\" |\"Dreaming\" \n| 3  || \u2014 \n|-\n|scope=\"row\" |\"Crazy4s\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=008&aid=0002480496|script-title=ko:'\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud558\uc774' \uae40\uc218\ud604, \uc218\uc9c0 \ub300\uc2e0 \uc740\uc815\uacfc \ub208\ub9de\uc558\ub124|date=16 February 2011|website=MT|language=ko}}</ref> \n<small>(Commercial song recorded for his Spris spring ad along with [[Hahm Eun-jung|Eun-jung]])</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 \n|scope=\"row\"|''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" |2012\n|scope=\"row\" |\"The One and Only You (\uadf8\ub300 \ud55c \uc0ac\ub78c)\"\n| 2 || 2<ref name=\"March 31, 2012 Billboard K-Pop Hot 100\">{{cite web |title=March 31, 2012 Billboard K-Pop Hot 100 |url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2012-03-31/k-pop-hot-100 |work=[[Korea K-Pop Hot 100]]|language=Korean |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> \n|scope=\"row\" |''[[Moon Embracing the Sun#Original soundtrack|Moon Embracing the Sun: Original Sound Track]]''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\" |\"Another Way (\ub610 \ub2e4\ub978 \uae38)\" \n| 119 || 38 \n|scope=\"row\" |''[[Another Way: Secret Version]]''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\"|\"Marine Boy\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=311&aid=0000132498|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604 '\ub9c8\ub9b0\ubcf4\uc774' \uacf5\uac1c, \ubc15\ud0dc\ud658 \uc751\uc6d0 \uc704\ud574 \uac00\ucc3d\ub825 \ud3ed\ubc1c|date=14 June 2012|website=Xports News|language=ko}}</ref> \n<small>(Official [[2012 Summer Olympics]] commercial song in South Korea to support swimmer [[Park Tae-hwan]])</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 \n|scope=\"row\" |''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\" |\"Winter Wonderland\"\n<small>(Commercial song recorded for his [[Tous Les Jours]] winter ad)</small>\n| \u2014 || \u2014 \n|scope=\"row\" |''Non-album Single''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" |2014\n|scope=\"row\" |\"In Front of Your House (\ub108\uc758 \uc9d1 \uc55e)\"\n| 3 || 4<ref name=\"Kim Soo Hyun Billboard Chart History\">{{cite web |title=Kim Soo Hyun Billboard Chart History |url=http://www.billboard.com/artist/5915839/kim-soo-hyun/chart |work=[[Billboard Hot 100]]|language=Korean |accessdate=24 June 2014}}</ref> \n|rowspan=\"2\" |''[[My Love from the Star#Original soundtrack|My Love from the Star: Original Sound Track]]''\n|-\n|scope=\"row\" |\"Promise (\uc57d\uc18d)\"\n| 12 || 13<ref name=\"Kim Soo Hyun Billboard Chart History\"/> \n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|colspan=\"13\" | \"\u2014\" denotes releases that were not released in that region\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Kim Soo-hyun}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Kim Soo-hyun}}\n* {{official website|http://soo-hyun.com/}} {{in lang|ko|en}}\n\n{{Forbes Korea Power Celebrity}}\n{{Baeksang Arts Award Best New Actor Film}}\n{{Baeksang Arts Award Best Actor Television}}\n{{Baeksang Arts Award for Most Popular Actor}}\n{{Grand Bell Awards for Best New Actor}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kim, Soo-hyun}}\n[[Category:South Korean male film actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male musical theatre actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean male television actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean television presenters]]\n[[Category:Chung-Ang University alumni]]\n[[Category:South Korean Roman Catholics]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century South Korean male actors]]\n[[Category:South Korean bowling players]]\n", "text_old": "{{other people}}\n{{short description|South Korean actor}}\n{{distinguish|Kim So-hyun}}\n{{Korean name|Kim}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name            = Kim Soo-hyun\n| image           = Kim Soo-hyun 2014 PaekSang Arts Awards06b.jpg\n|caption= At [[Baeksang Arts Awards]], May 2014\n| birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1988|2|16}}\n| birth_place     = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| education = \n| alma_mater      = [[Chung-Ang University]]\n| occupation      = Actor\n| years_active    = 2007\u2013present\n| agent           = {{hlist|[[KeyEast]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002014249|script-title=ko:'\uc720\ub9dd\uc8fc' \uae40\uc218\ud604, \ubc30\uc6a9\uc900 \uc774\ub098\uc601\uacfc \ud55c\uc1a5\ubc25|date=4 January 2010|website=Star Money|language=ko}}</ref>|[[Gold Medalist (company)|Gold Medalist]]}}\n|parents = \n| website         = {{url|http://soo-hyun.com/}}\n| module          = {{Infobox Korean name|child=yes|color=transparent\n| hangul          = {{linktext|\uae40|\uc218|\ud604}}\n| hanja           = {{linktext|\u91d1|\u79c0|\u8ce2}}\n| rr              = Kim Su-hyeon\n| mr              = Kim Suhy\u014fn\n}}\n| signature       = Kim Soo Hyun Signature.png\n}}\n\n'''Kim Soo-hyun''' ({{ko-hhrm|\uae40\uc218\ud604|\u91d1\u79c0\u8ce2}}; born February 16, 1988) is a South Korean actor best known for his roles in the television dramas ''[[Dream High]]'' (2011), ''[[Moon Embracing the Sun]]'' (2012), ''[[My Love from the Star]]'' (2013) and ''[[The Producers (TV series)|The Producers]]'' (2015), as well as the films ''[[The Thieves]]'' (2012), ''[[Secretly, Greatly]]'' (2013) and ''[[Real (2017 film)|Real]]'' (2017).\n\nKim was [[Gallup (company)|Gallup]] Korea's Actor of the Year in 2014.<ref>{{cite news| last=Park| first=Dong-je| script-title=ko:\uc774\uc720\ub9ac, \uae40\uc218\ud604 \uc774\uc5b4 '\uc62c\ud574\ub97c \ube5b\ub0b8 \ud0e4\ub7f0\ud2b8' 2\uc704 \uc120\uc815..\uc9c4\uc815\ud55c '\ub300\uc138' \ud655\uc778| url=http://www.breaknews.com/sub_read.html?uid=342835&section=sc4| accessdate=2014-12-27| work=BreakNews| date=23 December 2014|language=ko}}</ref> He was first included in the [[Forbes Korea Power Celebrity|''Forbes'' Korea Power Celebrity]] list in 2013 placing fourth,<ref>{{cite web|author=Ed Slott |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/timferguson/2013/04/25/k-pop-meets-michael-milken/ |title=Forbes Korea Power Celebrity 2013 |work=[[Forbes]] |date= |accessdate=2017-02-27}}</ref> and subsequently ranking second in 2015,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://jmagazine.joins.com/forbes/view/305259 |script-title=ko:\uc911\uc559\uc2dc\uc0ac\ub9e4\uac70\uc9c4 |work=[[JoongAng Ilbo]]|date=23 February 2015 |accessdate=2017-02-27|language=ko}}</ref> and fifth in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/19626925 |script-title=ko:1\uc704 \uc9c0\ud0a8 \uc5d1\uc18c, \ub2e8\uc228\uc5d0 \uc815\uc0c1\uad8c \uc624\ub978 \uc720\uc544\uc778\u00b7\ud61c\ub9ac |work=[[JoongAng Ilbo]] |date=25 February 2016 |accessdate=2017-02-27|language=ko}}</ref> The business magazine's Asia edition also listed him in its 30 under 30 in 2016.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carolinehoward/2016/02/24/g-e-m-angelababy-soo-hyun-kim-and-the-actors-and-athletes-of-30-under-30-asia/#669e37f1455b|title=G.E.M., Angelababy, Soo-hyun Kim And The Actors And Athletes Of 30 Under 30 Asia|last=Howard|first=Caroline|work=Forbes|access-date=2017-03-14}}</ref> The success of his television dramas throughout Asia established him as a top [[Korean Wave|Hallyu]] star.\n\n==Early life and education==\nKim's mother encouraged him to take acting classes during his high school years to help him overcome his introverted personality. His father is Kim Chung-hoon and was the lead singer of the 80's band \"Seven Dolphins\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/4773/kim-soo-hyuns-school-years-examined|title=What Was Kim Soo Hyun Like as a Student?|website=enewsWorld|date=27 March 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714111442/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/4773/kim-soo-hyuns-school-years-examined|archivedate=14 July 2014}}</ref> He enrolled at [[Chung-Ang University]]'s Film and Theater Department in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|title=KIM Soo-hyun, hero of SECRETLY GREATLY|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/interview.jsp?blbdComCd=601019&seq=46&mode=INTERVIEW_VIEW|website=Korean Film Biz Zone|date=18 June 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, it was revealed to the public that Kim has a paternal half-sister named [[Kim Ju-na]], a singer.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/95837/Kim-Soo-Hyun%E2%80%B2s-Half-Sister-Almost-Debuted-with-Girl-Group-The-Ark|title=Kim Soo Hyun\u2032s Half Sister Almost Debuted with Girl Group The Ark|date=22 July 2015|website=enewsWorld}}</ref> His cousin, Lee Sa-rang (real name Lee Jae-hyun), directed his latest film, ''[[Real (2017 film)|Real]]'' (2017).<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:\"\uc81c\uc791\u00b7\uc5f0\ucd9c\u00b7\uc5f0\uae30, \ud615\uc81c\uac00 \ub2e4\ud588\ub2e4\"\u2026'\ub9ac\uc5bc', \uac00\uc871\uacbd\uc601\uc758 \ub098\uc05c \uc608|url=http://m.entertain.naver.com/read?oid=433&aid=0000032513|website=Dispatch|language=ko|date=3 July 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/90105/N-Sonic%E2%80%99s-Zion-Revealed-to-Be-Kim-Soo-Hyun%E2%80%99s-Cousin|title=N-Sonic\u2019s Zion Revealed to Be Kim Soo Hyun\u2019s Cousin|date=26 May 2015|website=enewsWorld}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===2007\u20132010: Television career beginnings===\nKim made his television debut with a supporting role in the 2007 family sitcom ''[[Kimche Cheese Smile]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=213&aid=0000190429|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604 \"\ub370\ubdd4\uc791 '\uae40\uce58\uce58\uc988\uc2a4\ub9c8\uc77c', \ud5e4\uc5b4\uc2a4\ud0c0\uc77c \ub355\uc5d0 \uce90\uc2a4\ud305\"|date=18 March 2012|website=TV Report|language=ko}}</ref> and in 2008, landed a lead role in [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]'s critically acclaimed youth drama, ''[[Jungle Fish]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Yoon|first1=Go-eun|script-title=ko:\ubc15\ubcf4\uc601\u318d\uae40\uc218\ud604 \uc8fc\uc5f0 '\uc815\uae00\ud53c\uc26c' \ud2b9\ubcc4\uac1c\ubd09|url=http://www.yonhapnews.co.kr/culture/2010/09/16/0901000000AKR20100916184000005.HTML|work=[[Yonhap]]|language=Korean|trans-title=Special re-edit of Park Bo-young and Kim Soo-hyun\u2019s Jungle Fish|accessdate=2012-11-24|date=16 September 2010}}</ref> Based on a true story, it tackles the serious issues of school cheating, competitive academic standards, and interactive blogging in a fresh way.<ref name=jungle>{{cite web|last=Han|first=Sang-hee|title=Realism essential for local teen dramas|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/art/2010/09/135_73507.html|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=2012-11-23|date=26 September 2010}}</ref> The drama won a number of awards, including the [[Peabody Award]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.peabodyawards.com/award-profile/jungle-fish|title=Jungle Fish|work=[[Peabody Award|The Peabody Awards]]|accessdate=2014-06-01}}</ref><ref>[http://world.kbs.co.kr/english/program/program_musicnews_detail.htm?No=9426 \"''Jungle Fish'' Wins a Peabody\"], KBS World, 2 April 2009.</ref>\n\nFor the latter half of the year, Kim appeared in the food-based variety show [[Happy Sunday#Delicious Quiz!/A Taste Of Life|''Delicious Quiz'']] (also known as ''The Taste of Life'') as one of the hosts and in the [[short film]] ''Cherry Blossom''.\n\nIn 2009, Kim acted in the [[short film]] ''[[Worst Friends (2009 film)|Worst Friends]]'' by Namkoong Sun, which won the Best Film in Social Drama award at the Mise en Sc\u00e8ne Short Film Festival and the well-received [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] drama special ''[[Father's House]]'' where he acted alongside veteran actor [[Choi Min-soo]].<ref name=prof /> \nHe also co-hosted Mnet's ''[[Boys & Girls Music Countdown (South Korean TV program)|Boys & Girls Music Countdown]]'' along with [[Kara (South Korean band)|Kara]]'s [[Han Seung-yeon]] in 2009.<ref name=boys>{{cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/3307/kim-soo-hyun-and-karas-han-seung-yeon-co-mcs|title=Kim Soo Hyun and Kara's Han Seung Yeon Co-MCs?|website=enewsWorld|date=8 February 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140714202551/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/3307/kim-soo-hyun-and-karas-han-seung-yeon-co-mcs|archivedate=14 July 2014}}</ref>\n\nKim raised his profile through memorable turns as the younger version of the male lead characters in ''[[Will It Snow for Christmas?]]''<ref name=prof>[http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2010011215172346067 MY NAME IS: Kim Soo-hyun].''10Asia''. 12 January 2010.</ref> and ''[[Giant (TV series)|Giant]]'',  the latter winning him the Best New Actor award at the [[SBS Drama Awards]].<ref name=sbs>{{cite web|last=Ko|first=Kyoung-seok|title=Ko Hyun-jung wins grand prize at SBS Drama Awards|url=http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011010309120570290|work=10Asia|accessdate=2013-03-21|date=3 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===2011\u20132013: Rising popularity and breakthrough===\n[[File:Kim Soo-hyun at the Seoul Drama Awards, 4 September 2014 02.JPG|thumb|upright|In September 2014]]\nKim became a household name in 2011 after starring in teen musical drama ''[[Dream High]]''. He plays a country bumpkin who turned out to be a musical genius.<ref name=dream>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/4853|title=Kim Soo-hyun cast as male lead in upcoming KBS drama|date=1 November 2010|website=10Asia}}</ref> The drama brought in high domestic ratings<ref>{{cite web|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1101190067|script-title=ko:\ud0c4\ub825\ubc1b\uc740 '\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud558\uc774', 1\uc778\uc790 \uad73\ud788\uae30?|date=19 January 2011|work=Osen|language=ko}}</ref> and was also popular overseas, winning several international awards. As the only young actor in a cast of [[Korean pop idol|idols]], Kim studied song and dance for three months at [[JYP Entertainment]] to pull off the required scenes in the drama.<ref>[http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011031516383866168 INTERVIEW: Actor Kim Soo-hyun \u2013 Part 1], ''10Asia'', 15 March 2011.</ref><ref>[http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2011031515032638509 INTERVIEW: Actor Kim Soo-hyun \u2013 Part 2], ''10Asia'', 15 March 2011.</ref> He recorded two songs for the drama's soundtrack, his solo \"Dreaming\" as well as the title track \"Dream High\" with the rest of the cast.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.mk.co.kr/newsRead.php?year=2011&no=99452|title= \uae40\uc218\ud604 \uc9c1\uc811 \ubd80\ub978 `\ub4dc\ub9bc\ud558\uc774` OST `Dreaming` \uc778\uae30 \uae09\uc0c1\uc2b9|date=26 February 2011|website=Maeil Business Newspaper|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nKim's popularity skyrocketed when he starred in the hit period drama ''[[Moon Embracing the Sun]]'' as the young King Leehwon.<ref name=moon>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/9100|title=Kim Soo-hyun to turn king in new series|date=1 November 2011|website=10Asia}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Lee|first=Jin-ho|title=Kim Soo Hyun Cast in ''The Sun and the Moon''|url=http://enewsworld.mnet.com/enews/contents.asp?idx=1502|accessdate=|newspaper=enewsWorld|date=11 November 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150202133810/http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/1502/kim-soo-hyun-cast-in-the-sun-and-the-moon|archivedate=2 February 2015}}</ref> The drama recorded a peak rating of 42.2 percent,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2950005|title=Hit drama ends with record ratings|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=17 March 2012}}</ref> thereby earning the \"national drama\" status. Kim contributed his vocals to the soundtrack with the traditional ballad \"Only You\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2949695|title=Kim Soo-hyun sings on 'Moon Embracing the Sun' drama|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=12 March 2012}}</ref> and the more modern composition \"Another Way\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2949880|title=Kim Soo-hyun releases two singles in two days|date=15 March 2012|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]}}</ref>\n\nDue to his popularity, he set a new record in product endorsements for being the face of 17 products simultaneously.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2952539|title=Kim Soo-hyun sets new record for product endorsements|last=|first=|date=13 March 2012|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|access-date=}}</ref> He also won the Best TV Actor award at the 2012 [[Baeksang Arts Awards]]. Beating out heavyweight veterans such as [[Han Suk-kyu]], [[Shin Ha-kyun]] and [[Cha Seung-won]], Kim said \"I am very grateful for this moment, but I am ashamed as well. It's like getting a lot of homework. I'll keep trying to become a better actor in order to remain worthy of this award\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2952100|title=Kim Soo-hyun's win is hotly debated|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=28 April 2012}}</ref>\n\nKim made his big-screen debut in the star-studded heist film ''[[The Thieves]]'', touted by the press as the Korean version of ''[[Ocean's Eleven (2001 film)|Ocean's Eleven]]''.<ref name=thieves>{{cite web|url=http://en.tenasia.com/archives/6503|title=Kim Soo-hyun joins cast of high-profile movie|date=21 March 2011|website=10Asia}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2954303|title='The Thieves' all-star cast set to steal show|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=13 June 2012}}</ref> With over 12.9 million ticket sales, the film became the second highest-grossing movie in Korean film history.<ref>{{cite web|title=''The Thieves'' Emerges as Most Popular Korean Movie|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2012/10/04/2012100400835.html|accessdate=18 November 2012|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=4 October 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, Kim was cast to play the role of a North Korean spy who infiltrated South Korea as a village idiot in the movie ''[[Secretly, Greatly]]'', an adaptation of the popular [[webtoon]] series ''Covertness'' by Hun.<ref name=secretly>[http://www.asiae.co.kr/news/view.htm?idxno=2012043017541551050 Kim Soo-hyun lands role of North Korean spy in new movie]. ''10Asia''. 30 April 2012.</ref> The film broke several records and was one of the most successful box office hits of the year.<ref>{{cite web|title=''Secretly Greatly'' Blazes Trail at Box Office by Tapping Teen Audience|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2013/06/10/2013061001331.html|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|accessdate=2013-06-10|date=10 June 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Yun|first=Suh-young|title=''Secretly'' success shows teen power at box office|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2013/06/141_137220.html|work=[[The Korea Times]]|accessdate=2013-06-19|date=10 June 2013}}</ref> Kim won Best New Actor awards at the 50th [[Grand Bell Awards]] and the 50th [[Baeksang Arts Awards]].<ref name=baeksang>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140527001728|title=Kim Soo-hyun named best new movie actor in Baeksang awards|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=27 May 2014}}</ref><ref name=grand>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&seq=2748|title=THE FACE READER Picks Up 6 at 50th Grand Bell Awards|work=Korean Film Biz Zone|date=4 November 2013|access-date=6 March 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150408194424/http://www.koreanfilm.or.kr/jsp/news/news.jsp?mode=VIEW&seq=2748|archive-date=8 April 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===2014\u2013present: International fame===\n[[File:Kim Soo-hyun 2014 PaekSang Arts Awards32 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Baeksang Arts Awards May 2014]]\nFrom 2013 to early 2014, Kim starred in [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] fantasy romance series ''[[My Love from the Star]]'' alongside [[Jun Ji-hyun]].<ref name=star>{{cite web|title=Kim Soo-hyun, Jun Ji-hyun to Pair Up in New Drama|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2013/11/16/2013111600450.html|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=16 November 2013}}</ref> He also released two singles for the drama's soundtrack, titled \"In Front of Your House\" and \"Promise\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tenasia.hankyung.com/archives/217348|title=\uae40\uc218\ud604\uc774 \ubd80\ub978 \u2018\ubcc4\uadf8\ub300\u2019 OST \u2018\ub108\uc758 \uc9d1\uc55e\u2019 \uacf5\uac1c|date=19 February 2014|website=TenAsia|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=111&aid=0000370170|title=\uae40\uc218\ud604 \uc138\ub808\ub098\ub370 \ub4e3\ub294\ub2e4\u2026'\ubcc4\uadf8\ub300' OST '\uc57d\uc18d' \uacf5\uac1c|date=13 March 2014|website=Hankook Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref>\nThe drama had over three billion hits on the Chinese streaming website [[iQiyi]]<ref>{{cite web|last1=Shin|first1=Kyun-jin|first2=Sung-hee|last2=Yang|title=Hallyu booming again in China, bigger than ever|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2986309|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=14 March 2013}}</ref> and also sparked trends in fashion, make-up and restaurants.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/chinarealtime/2014/02/26/korean-tv-show-sparks-chicken-and-beer-craze-in-china/|title=Korean TV Show Sparks Chicken and Beer Craze in China|work=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=26 February 2014}}</ref> Kim experienced explosive growth in popularity throughout Asia<ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131736564494276_2|title=Hallyu trio captivate Chinese hearts|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|date=13 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/06/19/2014061901486.html|title=Who Are the Most Popular Korean Stars Overseas?|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=19 June 2014}}</ref> and became one of the most in-demand endorsers with 35 product endorsements.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2014/01/30/2014013000282.html|title=Kim Soo-hyun Is Advertisers' Favorite|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=30 January 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.meradio.sg/musicportal/musicNews/kim-soo-hyun-snaps-up-35/1165106.html|title=Kim Soo Hyun snaps up 35 endorsement deals!|last=|first=|date=24 November 2014|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|access-date=}}</ref> He won the ''Daesang'' (or \"Grand Prize\"), the highest award for television, at the 7th [[Korea Drama Awards]].<ref name=daesang>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2995614|title=Kim Soo-hyun wins at drama festival|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|date=3 October 2014}}</ref>\n\nFor the latter half of the year, Kim attended two international sports events. Held on 16 August 2014, Kim sang the official theme song \"Light up the Future\" with several artists at the opening ceremony of the [[2014 Summer Youth Olympics|2014 Summer Youth Olympic Games]] held in Nanjing, China.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140818000706|title=Kim Soo-hyun performs at Nanjing Youth Olympic Games opening ceremony|work=[[The Korea Herald]]|accessdate=12 September 2015}}</ref> He also participated in the opening ceremony of the [[2014 Asian Games opening ceremony|2014 Asian Games]] in Incheon, South Korea. Along with  actor [[Jang Dong-gun]], Korean opera singer Ahn Sook-sun and people from 45 nations, they delivered the message of \"One Asia\" at the second part of the highlight stage.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/sports/2014/09/207_163713.html|title=Hallyu stars to light up Asia opening ceremony|work=[[The Korea Times]]|date=27 August 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2015, Kim starred in [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]' variety drama ''[[The Producers (TV series)|The Producers]]'', written by ''My Love From the Star'' writer [[Park Ji-eun]].<ref name=producers>{{cite web|last1=Kim|first1=Jae-heun|title=Kim Soo-hyun returns in ''Producers''|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2015/05/201_178721.html|website=[[The Korea Times]]|date=11 May 2015}}</ref> The drama drew solid domestic ratings domestically, and was also sold to several countries internationally.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hancinema.net/-producers-sold-out-globally-82855.html|title='Producers' sold out globally|work=[[HanCinema]]|date=4 June 2015|publisher=Star News}}</ref> Kim once again won the Daesang (or \"Grand Prize\") at the 8th [[Korea Drama Awards]], 4th [[APAN Star Awards]] and the 2015 KBS Drama Awards for his acting performance.<ref name=korea>{{cite web|title=Kim Soo-hyun, Kim Tae-hee to headline Korean drama fest|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/culturesports/2015/09/09/0701000000AEN20150909008800315.html|website=[[Yonhap News Agency]]|accessdate=12 September 2015|date=9 September 2015}}</ref><ref name=apan>{{cite web|last1=Sung|first1=So-young|title=Kim Soo-hyun takes top APAN Star honors|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=3012149|website=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]|accessdate=2015-12-10|date=30 November 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20160101000100|title=Kim Soo-hyun grabs grand prize at KBS drama awards|date=1 January 2016|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref>\nKim was listed under ''[[Forbes]]'' \"30 Under 30 Asia 2016 list\" which comprises 30 influential people under 30 years old who have made substantial effect in their fields.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mwave.me/en/news/news/view/103393/the-charms-of-forbes-30-under-30-asia-kim-soo-hyun-g-dragon-and-snsd-s-yoona?_sorting=null&_cnMtCtgyId=null&_searchKeyWord=null&_position=null|title=The Charms of Forbes\u2032 \u203230 Under 30 Asia\u2032 Kim Soo Hyun, G-Dragon and SNSD\u2032s Yoona|date=11 March 2016|website=enewsWorld}}</ref>\n\nKim then starred in the action-noir film ''[[Real (2017 film)|Real]]'', which premiered in June 2017.<ref name=real>{{cite web|url=http://koreanfilm.or.kr/eng/news/news.jsp?pageIndex=1&blbdComCd=601006&seq=3399&mode=VIEW&returnUrl=&searchKeyword=|title=KIM Soo-Hyun Chooses Noir Flick for His Return|date=14 April 2015|website=Korean Film Biz Zone}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2017/06/27/0200000000AEN20170627006700315.html|title=(Yonhap Interview) Actor Kim Soo-hyun: 'I'm still clumsy but try to be closer to perfection'|date=27 June 2017|website=Yonhap News Agency}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, reports have surfaced that Kim is leaving KeyEast to form an agency with his cousin.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/12/688_280228.html|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun to set up own agency|date=December 12, 2017|website=The Korea Times}}</ref> In January 2020, Kim signed with [[Gold Medalist (company)|Gold Medalist]] along with actors [[Kim Sae-ron]] and [[Seo Ye-ji]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=3072120|title=Kim Soo-hyun signs a new contract|date=January 2, 2020|website=Korea JoongAng Daily}}</ref> \n\nIn 2020, Kim is set to star in the tvN drama ''[[It's Okay to Not Be Okay]]'' as a psychiatric aide. This will be his first small screen appearance in five years since ''The Producers''.<ref name=psy>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20200207000504|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun to star in tvN drama \u2018Psycho but It\u2019s Okay\u2019|date=February 7, 2020|website=The Korea Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajudaily.com/view/20200207132136323|title=Fans await Hallyu star Kim Soo-hyun's full comeback through TV drama|date=February 7, 2020|website=Aju Daily}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\n===Ambassadorial roles===\n*On 28 April 2011, Kim and [[Bae Suzy]] were officially revealed to be the ambassadors of the \"16th Goyang Korea Flower Show\" in the Gyeonggi Province.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ajunews.com/common/redirect.jsp?newsId=20110515000133|script-title=ko:\uace0\uc591\uaf43\uc804\uc2dc\ud68c 1\ucc9c\ub9cc\ub2ec\ub7ec \uacc4\uc57d 15\uc77c \ud3d0\ub9c9|date=15 May 2011|website=Aju News|language=ko}}</ref>\n* On 18 April 2012, the [[Korea Tourism Organization]] (KTO) appointed Kim as the Promotional Ambassador for Korean tourism.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/Article.aspx?aid=2951647|title=Kim Soo-hyun is new face of Korea|date=19 April 2012|work=[[Korea JoongAng Daily]]}}</ref> \n*On 20 May 2014, Kim was appointed as one of the public relations officer for his alma mater, Chung-Ang University.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=102&oid=032&aid=0002479439|script-title=ko:\uc911\uc559\ub300 \uc5ed\ub300\uae09 \ucd5c\uac15 \ud64d\ubcf4\ub300\uc0ac\u2026\uae40\uc218\ud604\u00b7\uc720\ub9ac\u00b7\uc218\uc601\u00b7\ubc15\uc2e0\ud61c \uc704\ucd09|date=20 May 2014|website=Khan|language=ko}}</ref>\n* On 25 October 2014, Kim was appointed as the Goodwill Ambassador of [[Seoul]]. For the city's promotion, he participated in various cultural events in the next two years.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201410091345102218777_2|title=Kim Soo-hyun becomes honorary ambassador of Seoul|date=9 October 2014|work=[[The Korea Herald]]}}</ref>\n* On 24 March 2015, Kim was named honorary ambassador for the Incheon International Airport.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201503241652523830709_2|title=Kim Soo-hyun named honorary ambassador for Incheon Airport|date=24 March 2015|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref>\n\n===Endorsements===\n*On 3 December 2012, Kim was appointed the ambassador for Lotte Hotel Busan.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.naver.com/main/read.nhn?mode=LSD&mid=sec&sid1=101&oid=003&aid=0004859130|script-title=ko:\ube44\uc2a4\ud2b8, \ubd80\uc0b0\ub86f\ub370\ud638\ud154\uc11c \ud32c\ubbf8\ud305|date=3 December 2012|website=Newsis|language=ko}}</ref> \n* On 29 April 2016, Kim was selected as an ambassador of Paradise City.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businesskorea.co.kr/news/articleView.html?idxno=14449|title=Paradise Group Selects Kim Soo-hyun as Paradise City Ambassador|date=19 April 2016|website=Business Korea}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\n===Bowling===\nA bowling enthusiast, Kim applied to become a professional bowler in October 2016. He ranked 10th out of the 114 participants on his first try-out tournament but failed to make the cut on the second, falling short of the 200 points needed to qualify with only 192.3.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2016/10/201_216003.html |title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun wants to be professional bowler |work=[[The Korea Times]] |date=13 October 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2016/10/31/2016103100790.html |title=Kim Soo-hyun Fails to Make Cut at Pro-Bowling Tryouts  |work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]] |date=31 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Military enlistment===\nKim enlisted as an active duty soldier and began his [[Conscription in South Korea|mandatory military service]] on October 23, 2017.\nHe entered a military camp in Paju, Gyeonggi Province to complete his basic training.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/news/2017/10/23/0200000000AEN20171023002700315.html|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun joins military|date=23 October 2017|work=Yonhap News Agency|accessdate=2017-10-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2017/10/24/2017102400814.html|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun Starts Military Service|date=24 October 2017|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201709281757263389043_2|title=Kim Soo-hyun to enlist on Oct. 23|date=28 September 2017|work=Kpop Herald}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201710301403286624753_2&ACE_SEARCH=1|title=Photo of Kim Soo-hyun in military uniform released|date=30 October 2017|website=Kpop Herald}}</ref> In late November 2017, his agency announced that Kim had completed his five weeks basic training placing fourth as an outstanding trainee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2017112914081861040&VBC|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604, \uc6b0\uc218\ud6c8\ub828\ubcd1 \uae30\ucd08\uad70\uc0ac\ud6c8\ub828 \ub05d..\uc218\uc0c9\ub300\ub300 \uc790\uc6d0|author=Lee Kyung-ho|date=29 November 2017|work=Star News|language=ko}}</ref> He  was assigned to the 1st Reconnaissance Battalion to continue his duty.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news1.kr/articles/?3166383|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604 \uce21 \"\uc218\uc0c9\ub300\ub300\ub85c \uc790\ub300\ubc30\uce58\u2026\uc6b0\uc218 \ud6c8\ub828\ubcd1 \ubf51\ud600 \ud3ec\uc0c1\ud734\uac00\" [\uacf5\uc2dd]|date=29 November 2017|work=News1|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/22160975|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604 \uce21 \"\uc218\uc0c9\ub300\ub300\ub85c \uc790\ub300\ubc30\uce58\u2026\uc6b0\uc218 \ud6c8\ub828\ubcd1 \ubf51\ud600 \ud3ec\uc0c1\ud734\uac00\" [\uacf5\uc2dd]|date=29 November 2017|website=News Joins|language=ko|author=Yeo Hyun-goo|publisher=JoongAng Daily}}</ref> In February 2019, Kim received an early promotion as a [[Sergeant]] for his exceptional conduct in the military.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pop.heraldcorp.com/view.php?ud=201903041635539187608_1|title=[\ub2e8\ub3c5]\uae40\uc218\ud604\u00b7\uc625\ud0dd\uc5f0, \ubcd1\uc7a5 \uc870\uae30\uc9c4\uae09\u2026\uc131\uc2e4\ud55c \uad70\uc0dd\ud65c \ub355\ubd84|website=Pop Herald|access-date=2019-04-03|date= March 4, 2019|author=Go Myung-jin}}</ref> Kim was discharged on July 1, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koreatimes.co.kr/www/art/2019/06/688_270376.html|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun to be discharged July 1|date=10 June 2019|website=The Korea Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2019/07/02/2019070201131.html|title=Actor Kim Soo-hyun Discharged from Military|date=2 July 2019|website=The Chosun Ilbo}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! Ref. \n|-\n| 2008\n| ''Cherry Blossom''\n| Han Hyun-joon\n| rowspan=\"2\" |[[Short film]]\n| \n|-\n| 2009\n| ''[[Worst Friends (2009 film)|Worst Friends]]'' \n| Kim Joon-ki\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.joins.com/article/7552571|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604\u00b7\uc815\uc18c\ubbfc, \uacfc\uac70 \ub2e8\ud3b8 \uc601\ud654 \ucd9c\uc5f0 \ubaa8\uc2b5 \u2018\ub208\ube5b\uc774\u2026\u2019|date=7 March 2012|website=JoongAng Ilbo|language=ko}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012 \n| ''[[The Thieves]]'' \n| Zampano\n|\n| <ref name=thieves /> \n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Secretly, Greatly]]''\n| Won Ryu-hwan / Bang Dong-gu\n|\n|<ref name=secretly /> \n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Miss Granny]]''\n| young Mr. Park \n|[[cameo appearance|Cameo]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hancinema.net/kim-soo-hyun-makes-cameo-appearance-in-movie-miss-granny-64621.html|title=Kim Soo-hyun makes cameo appearance in movie \"Miss Granny\"|date=6 January 2014|website=Hancinema|publisher=Xports News}}</ref> \n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Real (2017 film)|Real]]''\n| Jang Tae-young\n|\n|<ref name=real /> \n|}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Network\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2007 \n| ''[[Kimchi Cheese Smile]]'' \n| Kim Soo-hyun\n| [[Munhwa Broadcasting Corporation|MBC]] \n|\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.g-enews.com/view.php?ud=201511232137395965318_1|script-title=ko:\uae40\uc218\ud604, \uacfc\uac70 '\uae40\uce58\uce58\uc988\uc2a4\ub9c8\uc77c' \uc218\uc601\uc120\uc218\uc2dc\uc808 \ud0c4\ud0c4\ud55c \ubcf5\uadfc \uc7ac\uc870\uba85...'\uc800 \ubcf5\uadfc\uc5d0 \ube68\ub798